      "body" : "\"Wladimir J. van der Laan\" <notifications@github.com> writes:\n>> However, I've long through that a single testnet can't fullfill all functions we want from a testnet.\n>\n> I tend to agree. I also don't think it should be up to us define all kinds of testnet that should be possible.\n> In the future I'd imagine it'll be possible to load some chainparams from a .json file, which defines the rules and settings to join an arbitrary testnet (e.g. @jtimon's #8855 would be a first step there).\n> (of course the individual rules would have to be part of bitcoin core, but a testnet could pick and choose either wild-west conditions or stable as possible ones)\n\nIn practice you need to change rpcport and port, as well as whatever\nrules are needed for the testchain.  So I think a new conf is better\nthan a json file.\n\nMy original idea was that you would give a genesis blockhash and DNS\nseed or manually addnode.  The genesis block would tell you the other\nchain parameters.\n\nCheers,\nRusty.\n",
